element.name: O is for Overend by Hezekiah, Traditional Cache (1/1)

center.font: Visit the new Geocaching Ireland discussion forum HERE

element.long-description: Airfield was the home of the Overend family, most recently Letitia and Naomi (sisters), who lived there for their entire lives. They were very well known characters in the Dundrum locality, mainly thanks to their beautiful range of vintage cars, their pedigree herd of Jersey cows and, of course, for their altruistic endeavours, of which Airfield is a living testament. You can walk around the grounds and admire gardens, animals and cars, enjoy a meal in the restaurant or do some shopping - or you can stay in the car park and find the cache! There is an admission charge to the grounds, but it's worth it - take the time to view the estate. (€6 for adults; €3 for children - there are group and concession rates available also. The estate is open Tuesday to Saturday 10 - 4; Sunday and Bank Holidays 11 - 4). More info at www.airfield.ie
element.encoded-hints: Under ivy at the base of a small tree - 2 m away from a light in the car park.

2010-05-10T19:00:00Z : Found it by weitzclan
We came to drop Georgia's Travel SLuG and found the mini cooper - one in one out :-) Lovely spot and will probably be back to see the animals and the gardens (didn't fit with our plans on a wet and windy afternoon). TFTC Weitclan

2010-04-29T19:00:00Z : Found it by GreyHair&NoHair
Found this with our grandson, the cache was damp and could do with a new log! Watch out for muggles! TFTC

2010-04-05T19:00:00Z : Found it by Lynjas
We found this on our 3rd visit once we discovered it was near a tree and not just a stump. Nice cache - we visit this lovely spot frequently. TFTC

2008-10-11T19:00:00Z : Found it by Kersti.com
The area here is quite overgrown at the moment so took a long time to find the item that the clue mentioned. Once we found it (much smaller than expected) the cache was soon in hand. We then popped around to the tea rooms and hand a look in the shop before heading to the Sword in the Stone.
